I'm currently looping through a hubdb to make a google chart; in the last 3 lines i'm trying to make a rule where if `row.services` contains 'Auto Body' to set variable `categories` to include the string ", Auto Body" after the returned  `category.name` *is append the correct function?*

```['Member Type', 'Count'],
{% set table_info = hubdb_table_rows(2666166) %}
{% set cat_field = 'member_category' %}
{% set categories = hubdb_table_column(2666166, cat_field).options %}



{% for category in categories %}

  {# Setup count for current term #}
  {% set count = {'value': 0} %}
  {# Loop through the table #}
  {% for row in table_info %}
          {% if services is containing 'Auto Body' %}
          {% set categories = categories.append(, Auto Body) %}
          {% endif %}

  {% endfor %}['{{ category.name }}', {{ count.value }} ],{% endfor %}```
